The paper deals with scheduling algorithms for multiuser communication systems with multiple antennas and linear receivers, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses practical scheduling schemes based on signal-to-interference-and-noise ratio (SINR) feedback, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper presents new analysis of MRC, ZF and MMSE receivers, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.MM) and learning theory (cs.LG).
